    <title>Mint Chocolate Chip Ice Cream Recipe</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/recipestyle.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Mint Chocolate Chip Ice Cream</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 cups heavy cream</li>
            <li>1 cup whole milk</li>
            <li>3/4 cup granulated sugar</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon peppermint extract</li>
            <li>1 cup chocolate chips</li>
            <li>Green food coloring (optional)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>icecream</li>
            <li>dessert</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a mixing bowl, combine heavy cream, whole milk, granulated sugar, and peppermint extract. Mix well until the sugar dissolves.</li>
            <li>Add green food coloring if desired for a minty color.</li>
            <li>Chill the mixture in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours or until it is thoroughly chilled.</li>
            <li>Transfer the chilled mint mixture to an ice cream maker and churn according to the manufacturer's instructions.</li>
            <li>In the last few minutes of churning, add chocolate chips to the ice cream maker to incorporate them into the mixture.</li>
            <li>Once churned, transfer the mint chocolate chip ice cream to a lidded container and freeze for at least 4 hours or until firm.</li>
            <li>Scoop and enjoy the cool and minty Mint Chocolate Chip Ice Cream!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
